<br>
1. If a PC is in melée range of the mob, no mob will *ever* go for a Pet, they will always go for a Player.<br>
2. Normal agro rules do apply if you have a pet tanking and casters out of the mobs melée range.  You can nuke, heal, etc., as you would with any other tank. If they pet's damage and taunt is enough, the mob will ignore the nukers and healers<br>
3. Root negates this and forces mobs to hit the closest &quot;thing&quot; on its agro list - Pet or Player.<br>
<br>
Not entirely sure why Trevar feels the need to lie in the thread (other than groundless boasting, perhaps) but the above rules apply to all pets, all of the time.<br>
<br>
It's actually laziness on Verant's part.  One would not see all that much difficulty in coding a way of correctly allocating pets to the agro list as a PC is, allowing melée to participate when pets are being used to tank.  At one point Pets were always attacked first (the exact opposite of how it now is).  That was fun as pets can tank the most uber of mobs much better that players.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
