Every giant in Kael.  I hardly call that too situational an idea to be of value.  It lets you do what I did all day long in Kael if you wish, exactly what this thread was about.  I never said this applies to other mobs all over Norrath, I stated a case where it applies to Kael...  because this post was about &quot;DC pets tanking in Kael&quot;.  If this were a post about DC pets in some other zone, &quot;then&quot; DC pets and how they act in Kael wouldn't have applied.<br>
<br>
&quot;And losing rounds from out of range makes it pretty pointless as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
How does that equate to pointless exactly?  If I would have been in range the whole time taking hits we wouldn't have been able to do this, as the druid would not have been able to keep me healed.  THAT would be pretty pointless, as it most battles would equal death.  By losing a few hits here and there, I almost completely negated the need for our group to heal, slow, med, or tank.  Making an undoable sitation doable by making a small sacrifice (still did far more damage than I lost) is hardly pointless.  In fact, it has a VERY good point.  Without DC, that 3 set of classes would not have been able to hunt in that area for very long if at all (depends on how much mana and what heals that druid has).<br>
<br>
